members.name: periods
members.doc:
Times that this object is available. Each period represents a range of hours when the object is
available during the week. Limited to 100 time periods.

members.name: totalFailures
members.doc: For how many items the requested action was not successful

members.name: totalSuccesses
members.doc: For how many items the requested action was successful

members.name: undetailedFailures
members.doc: total number of failures without details because detailed-failure-threshold exceeded

members.name: draftPublishedDate
members.doc: date and time in UTC `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: locationId
members.doc: The location id that the catalog refers to

members.name: revision
members.doc: Catalog revision, represents the number of changes to the catalog.

members.name: availableChoices
members.doc: List of available choices for the option.

members.name: price
members.doc: Option price. When an option price is included in the item price, price = null.

members.name: availableChoices
members.doc: List of available choices for the option.

members.name: maxChoices
members.doc: Max number of options allowed to be chosen for this item. default available_choices size, must be equal or bigger than min choices

members.name: minChoices
members.doc: Number of options required to be chosen for this item. default 0, max value is available_choices size

members.name: error
members.doc: In case of failure, details about the error

members.name: originalIndex
members.doc: The index of the item within the request array to allow the caller to correlate the request and response items

members.name: success
members.doc: Whether the action requested was successful for this item. When this value is false, error should be populated

members.name: archived
members.doc: Whether the catalog is archived or not. False by default

members.name: locationIds
members.doc: Location filter. Pass an array of location IDs to return catalogs with any of the provided locations.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Defaults to offset = 0 and limit = 50 (max limit 1,000).

members.doc: Whether the item is archived or not. Default value is false

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency code. Must be valid ISO 4217 currency code (e.g., USD).

members.name: formattedValue
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string in local format (e.g., 1 000,30). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: value
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

description:
Money.
Default format to use. Sufficiently compliant with majority of standards: w3c, ISO 4217, ISO 20022, ISO 8583:2003.

description: Set of time periods when a object availability hours differ from its normal availability hours.

members.name: closeDay
members.doc: Day of the week this period ends on.

members.name: closeTime
members.doc:
Time in 24hr ISO 8601 extended format (hh:mm). Valid values are 00:00-24:00, where 24:00 represents
midnight at the end of the specified day field.

members.name: openDay
members.doc: Day of the week this period starts on.

members.name: openTime
members.doc:
Time in 24hr ISO 8601 extended format (hh:mm). Valid values are 00:00-24:00, where 24:00 represents
midnight at the end of the specified day field.

description:
A span of time that the object is available,
starting on the specified open day/time and closing on the specified close day/time.
Closing time must occur after the opening time, for example later in the same day, or on a subsequent day.
